<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<section xml:id="chp2sec1" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>The Division Algorithm</title>

  <p> </p>

    <definition xml:id="definition-divisibility">
    <title>Divisibility</title>
    <statement>
        <p>
            An integer <m> a </m> is <term>divisible</term> by an integer <m>b</m> if there exists an integer <m>c</m> so that <m>a=bc</m>.  
        </p>

        <p>
          If <m> a </m> is divisible by <m>b</m>, we say also say <m>b</m> <term>divides</term> <m>a</m>.  We symbolize this by <m>b\mid a</m>.  We say that <m>b</m> is a <term>divisor</term> of <m>a</m>.
        </p>

        <p>
          If <m>b</m> does not divide <m>a</m>, then we write <m>b\nmid a</m>. 
        </p>
    </statement>
  </definition>
  


<proposition xml:id="proposition-basic_divisibility">
  <title>Basic divisibilities</title>
  <statement>
    <p>
      If <m>a\in \Z</m> where <m>a\ne 0</m>, then 
      <ol>
        <li>
          <p>
            <m>1 \mid a </m>
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            <m>-1 \mid a </m>
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            <m>a \mid 0 </m>
          </p>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </p>
  </statement>
  <proof>
    <p>
      Try a direct proof.  Let the definitions structure your proof.  You may find  <xref ref="definition-divisibility"/>,   <xref ref="definition-commutative_ring"/>, <xref ref="proposition-zero_times_anything_is_zero"/>, and <xref ref="proposition-negative_one_times_anything_is_additive_inverse"/> useful.
    </p>
  </proof>
</proposition>



<proposition xml:id="proposition-divisibility_is_transitive">
  <title>Divisibility is transitive</title>
  <statement>
    <p>
      If <m>a,b,c\in \Z</m> where <m>a\mid b</m> and <m>b\mid c</m>, then <m>a\mid c</m>.
    </p>
  </statement>
  <proof>
    <p>
      Try a direct proof.  Let the definitions structure your proof.  You may find  <xref ref="definition-divisibility"/> and  <xref ref="definition-commutative_ring"/> useful.
    </p>
  </proof>
</proposition>

